message.content: "You misjudge me," said Barley. "You have nothing to tell me yet. But we'll be meeting again, no doubt, and then you will have. Regard this as a softening-up process and have dinner with me. On His Lordship, of course." "On one condition," said John. "Tell me who the little bird was." "Can't you guess? Whose portrait appears regularly in the shiny papers?"
